[[Image:Ovis orientalis aries 'Skudde' (aka).jpg|thumb|A domestic sheep]]

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} ''[[sceap|scēap]]'', from {{proto|Germanic}} *''skæpom'' (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} ''[[skiep]]'', {{etyl|nl|-}} ''[[schaap]]'', {{etyl|de|-}} ''[[Schaf]]''), from *''kæppi'' (compare {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|kjappi}} 'he-goat', {{etyl|de|-}} dialect ''Kippe'' 'newborn calf'), ultimately from Sarmato-Scythian (compare {{etyl|fa|-}} {{term|čapiš}} 'yearling goat', [[Ossetian]] ''cæw'' 'goat'); akin to {{etyl|sq|-}} ''c(j)ap, sqap'' 'he-goat', {{etyl|cu|-}} ''kapŭ''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP|US}} {{enPR|shēp}}, {{IPA|/ʃiːp/}}, {{SAMPA|/Si:p/}}
